parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turn Signal Lens Corrosion and Sealing Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion inside the turn signal lens can cause the lens to become cloudy or discolored, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, the failure of the lens to seal properly can allow water to enter, further exacerbating the corrosion and potentially causing electrical issues.
symptoms: Cloudy or discolored turn signal lens
water accumulation inside the turn signal lens
corrosion or rust visible inside the turn signal lens
turn signal lens does not seal properly.
